Rating: 2
I made this as directed in the recipe, and it won't come out like the picture if you do that. The main issue is the marinade is too thin to develop into a sauce in one hour of oven time; also, the juice from the ribs overwhelms the marinade in volume. As far as taste, it's decent but the cumin is what comes through, so if you don't like cumin, move on. (I love it!) Were I to use the marinade ingredients again, I'd probably do two things: 1) cook down the marinade on the stovetop until it is syrupy *before* applying to the meat, and 2) preheat the the baking dish and/or sear the ribs on the stove to keep the moisture from escaping. Bottom line: this recipe was not well conceived in terms of procedure, but there's a good rib recipe in there if you work on it.

