Rating: 4
Great recipe. I was in a hurry one evening and decided to try a short cut, skipping the marinating time and using an oven roasting bag: Mix marinade ingredients in large measuring cup until sugar dissolves. Cut racks into individual ribs and place in a large bowl. Pour marinade over ribs, stir to coat well. Prepare an oven roasting bag with recommended 1 T of flour, and place on a large roasting sheet. Pour ribs with marinade into bag. Carefully arrange ribs so they are, as much as possible, in a single layer. Be careful not to puncture the bag. Seal the bag with the provided tie, and snip a few vent holes in the top with scissors. Roast for 1 hour. Quick prep, no clean up. Delicious!

