Rating: 4
This recipe is really unique in that it would make a guest think that you spent gobs of time in the kitchen, when, in fact, there is virtually no labor involved!!! Used a scant pound of boneless country pork ribs that I trimmed of excess fat and cut into rib-sized strips. I made one-half of the marinate and chilled the strips in the fridge as written. Used an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish and roasted the rib strips at 400 degrees (we live at high altitude). I checked them at 25 minutes to see if it was time to turn them, and they were done!! Thickened the juice with a bit of cornstarch mixed with water, and covered them for 5 minutes while I finished up the rest of dinner--ya, ya--to heck with "hors d'oeuvre servings". These ribs, along with "Viennese Cucumber Salad" (from this site), and plain long-grain white rice, made a delicious super easy dinner for 2 when it was 104 degrees outside (and the oven didn't need to be on for very long!). Do try this recipe!! The meat was tender, juicy, and flavorful. Yum, Yum.

